  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Motor Claims Estimator",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><p>· Inspect and assess damaged vehicles to provide detailed and accurate repair estimates</p><p>· Liaise with insurance providers to obtain approvals and manage the claims process</p><p>· Communicate with customers to explain repair requirements and timelines</p><p>· Maintain detailed records of all repair estimates and claims activities</p><p>· Collaborate with the workshop team to ensure efficient and high-quality repairs</p><p>· Oversee vehicle checking for body and paintwork during the repair process in a timely manner</p><p>· Assist in the day-to-day operations of the motor claims department.</p><p>· Monitor the development of every claim and policy and ensure adherence to legal requirements, industry   </p><p>  regulations, and customer quality standards set by the company.</p><p>· To manage and control stocks in the store</p><p>· QC the Vehicle before releasing it back to the customer</p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><p>· Min 3 -5 years' experience as a Claims Estimator or preferably in the Automotive industry</p><p>· Strong technical knowledge of automotive repair processes and parts</p><p>· Excellent communication and customer service skills</p><p>· Proficient in using estimation software and computer systems</p><p>· Ability to work independently and as part of a team</p><p>· Organized and detail-oriented with good problem-solving skills</p><p>· Possess with Singapore Class 3 Driving licence preferably</p><p><br /></p>",
